Odessa Warren Grey https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odessa_Warren_Grey 0 Odessa Warren Grey (August 13, 1883 - April 28, 1960) was milliner, entrepreneur, and performer in Harlem, New York. She is best known as the star the silent film, Lime Kiln Field Day (1913) where she co-stars with Bert Williams.
